    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently:\n\n<img width=\"652\" height=\"287\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1cdff5a5-1ca6-4fba-83e9-5fe02bd08537\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSuggested:\n\n<img width=\"658\" height=\"364\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a4c4c66b-07ce-413b-aa9f-ed1e4385a813\" />\n\nBoth more correct and visually distinct from main text.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`{buffer}` and `{opts}` are recognized as arguments because of the `{}`. Not sure it would make sense to try to recognize the full function rather than explicitly surrounding it with backticks.\n\nThere is also potential for recognizing these cases as \"h4\":\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/tree-sitter-vimdoc/issues/110\n\n",
